This paper discusses the challenges of migrating datasets or applications between graph database systems, which is a common problem in the field of database management (cs.DB). The paper also proposes a formalisation of the Opencypher graph query language, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for standardisation in the field, which is a topic relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
